<P>Ignatius Donnelly (1831-1901), lawyer, land promoter,
politician and virtuoso author, is today best known for
his pioneering work on the subject of Atlantis, 
&quot;Atlantis the Antediluvian World&quot; (ATAW).
Published in 1882, ATAW is one of the best constructed
Atlantis theories, as it makes no recourse to occult or
'channeled' information. Donnelly's lucid style and command
of the facts (such as they were) make the book
readable and compelling even today....<SMALL>--JBH</SMALL></P>
